'''Tarah Lynne Schaeffer''' (born July 4, 1984) is an American actress. She is known for her role on ''[[Sesame Street]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|title= 'Street' Wise For 27 years, there's been a warm place in the hearts of children and parents for "Seaame Street.' Let's take a sunny day stroll. |last= Zurawik |first= David |date= November 18, 1996 |newspaper = [[The Baltimore Sun]] |url= http://articles.baltimoresun.com/1996-11-18/features/1996323080_1_fairy-godmother-sesame-street-noah-wyle/2 |access-date=January 2, 2017}}</ref>

She was cast in 1993 as the first ''Sesame Street'' cast member with disabilities &ndash; she was born with a disorder called [[osteogenesis imperfecta]]. She remained on the show for eight seasons.

